The paper proposes a framework for learning optimal search algorithms from data, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses partially-adaptive and non-adaptive strategies, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and information theory (cs.IT), respectively.
